              <DefinitionShort>a relative state of anger</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>anger</Gloss>
                <Gloss>fury</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages it is impossible to speak of ‘anger’ without indicating against whom the anger exists. For example, in {S:05400200800026} it might be possible to say ‘to pray without anger against anyone’ or ‘to pray without being angry at anyone.’</Comments>
